The paper deals with convolutional neural networks and their application to high-level tasks such as image classification, object detection, and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new joint training algorithm, which involves training a more global graphical model, which could fall under the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with structured networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
